2500|$|The initial {{funding for}} the Human Terrain System came from the Joint Improvised Explosive Device Defeat Organization (JIEDDO). The JIEDDO funding of $20 million, granted in the summer 2006, {{supported}} the pilot HTS project from mid-2006 to 2007. Following the Central Command JUONS request for the major and rapid expansion of HTS in April 2007, <b>the</b> <b>Defense</b> <b>Secretary</b> approved a $40 million expansion of HTS to be funded by the Department of Defense (DOD). [...] DOD provided HTS funding until 2009 when funding responsibilities were assumed by Army G2 (i.e., the Army's Military Intelligence budget). In 2009 {{it was reported that}} the annual budget for the program was $143 million. In May 2010 the HASC temporarily limited the funding obligation to HTS until the Army submitted an assessment of the program that addressed concerns that had been raised. In 2011, McFate stated that HTS had a $150 million annual budget.|$|E
